1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish the proactive governance framework for capacity and availability management within the Elko County Information Operations Department.
 This policy governs how the Department baselines current capacity and availability,
 forecasts future needs,
 and ensures that infrastructure can meet the service level commitments defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 before those commitments are at risk.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy is concerned with planning:
 establishing baselines,
 identifying trends,
 defining thresholds,
 and driving remediation before gaps become failures.
 Real-time monitoring and alerting against those thresholds is governed by 
\series bold
Policy 
