\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Capacity Baseline
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Department shall maintain a current capacity baseline across all in-scope resource categories:
 storage,
 compute,
 network bandwidth,
 and application performance.
 The baseline shall be established from measured actuals and updated no less than quarterly.
 The baseline is the authoritative reference point against which forecasting,
 trend analysis,
 and threshold calibration are conducted.
 The Assistant IT Director shall ensure the accuracy of the capacity baseline through quarterly validation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Availability Measurement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Availability shall be measured for all services with active SLA targets under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 Availability measurement shall distinguish planned downtime from unplanned downtime.
 The Assistant IT Director shall measure availability actuals against 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 SLA targets no less than monthly and shall update availability records to reflect current actuals in advance of each quarterly briefing.
 Availability data shall be made available to 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 reporting processes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Threshold Definition
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall define capacity and availability thresholds that,
 when breached,
 indicate risk to service level commitments.
 Threshold values shall be documented and provided to the 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.12"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 monitoring function for implementation in automated monitoring configurations.
 Threshold values shall be reviewed no less than annually or whenever a Significant or Emergency change (as defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
) is executed against the service catalog or infrastructure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Forecasting and Planning
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Department shall conduct forward-looking capacity and availability planning no less than annually.
 Planning shall be timed to inform the County budget cycle and shall account for known service changes,
 projected growth,
 and aging infrastructure.
 Where forecasting identifies a gap between projected capacity and committed service levels,
 the Assistant IT Director shall develop a remediation plan.
 Remediation plans requiring budget or infrastructure change shall be presented to the IT Director for approval before submission to the 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 change process.
 Emergency capacity issues requiring immediate infrastructure change shall be routed through the 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 Emergency change category.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5 Issue Response
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
When monitoring under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.12"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 identifies a threshold breach,
 the Assistant IT Director shall investigate and determine whether the breach represents a transient condition or a structural capacity or availability gap.
 The Assistant IT Director shall document transient conditions,
 including duration and impact,
 within the designated System of Engagement (Redmine) prior to closing the event.
 Structural gaps shall be addressed through the forecasting and planning process defined in Section 6.4.
\end_layout

